</head><msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104277 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111614 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91002492 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002009961"><summary>Miscellaneous collection of hagiographic works on prophets, saints, and imams, with special reference to the martyrs of 
            <placeName>Karbala</placeName>. Volume not dated; item a dated (27 Rajab 1230/5 July 1815). Scribal nastaʿlīq and shikastah āmīz. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged (combed marble paper with brown leather edging over delaminating and crumbling pasteboards), labels. Folios unbound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile.
                  </summary><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item1"><locus from="1v" to="92r">ff. 1v-92r</locus><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(a), ff. 1v-92r.</p><p>Hagiographic treatise collecting traditions and anecdotes relating to the patriarchs, prophets, caliphs, imams, saints, mystics, and kings, organised into thirty-three chapters, by 
                <persName key="viaf_46339081" role="aut">Sayf al-Ẓafar Nawbahārī</persName>.
                        </p><p>Dated colophon (f. 92r): completed at dawn on the morning of Thursday, 27 Rajab in RY9 of 
                <persName key="viaf_308694679" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Akbar II</persName>, 1230/5 July 1815.
                        </p><p>At the beginning (f. 1r) are three large vifq al-aʿdād or magic number squares (7 x 7; 8 x 8; 9 x 9).</p></note><author><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100168182472.0x000001 viaf_375164479580326210007">Sayf al-Ẓafar Nawbahārī</persName><persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_375164479580326210007">سيف الظّفر نوبهارى</persName></author><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3711">Durr al-majālis</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_3711">ردّ المجالس</title></msItem><msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item2"><locus from="93r" to="105r">ff. 93r-105r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(b), ff. 93r-105r.</p><p>Hagiographic treatise on the death of the Prophet 
                <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Muḥammad</persName>by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21802">Majlis-i avval dar vafāt-i Sayyid-i Kāʾināt ʿalayhi […]</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21802">مجلس اوّل در وفات سيّد كائنات عليه [...]</title></msItem><msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item3"><locus from="105r" to="112v">ff. 105r-112v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(c), ff. 105r-112v.</p><p>Hagiographic treatise on life and status of Lady 
                <persName key="viaf_30328354" role="subject">Fāṭimah</persName>, daughter of Prophet 
                <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Muḥammad</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21803">Majlis-i dūyum ḥikāyat-i Ḥaz̤rat-i Fāṭimah ʿalayhi al-salām</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21803">مجلس دويم حكايت حضرت فاطمه عليه السّلام</title></msItem><msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item4"><locus from="113r" to="121v">ff. 113r-121v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(d), ff. 113r-121v.</p><p>Hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of the Caliph and Imam 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657175.0x000001 viaf_34436377" role="subject">ʿAlī</persName>, husband of Lady 
                <persName key="viaf_30328354" role="subject">Fāṭimah</persName>, and cousin of Prophet 
                <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Muḥammad</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21804">Majlis-i sīvīm dar shihādat-i Amīr al-Muʾminīn ʿalayhi al-salām</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21804">مجلس سيويم در شهادت امير المؤمنين عليه السّلام</title></msItem><msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item5"><locus from="121v" to="129r">ff. 121v-129r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(e), ff. 121v-129r.</p><p>Hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_125394708" role="subject">Ḥasan</persName>, elder son and successor to Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="subject">ʿAlī</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21805">Majlis-i chahārum dar bayān-i shihādat-i Ḥaz̤rat-i Imām Ḥasan ʿalayhi al-salām</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21805">مجلس چهارم در بيان شهادت حضرت امام حسن عليه السّلام</title></msItem><msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item6"><locus from="129v" to="136v">ff. 129v-136v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(f), ff. 129v-136v.</p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_125394708" role="subject">Ḥasan</persName>, elder son and successor to Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="subject">ʿAlī</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item7"><locus from="137r" to="143r">ff. 137r-143r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(g), ff. 137r-143r.</p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of 
                <persName key="viaf_54030432" role="subject">Muslim</persName>, son of 
                <persName key="viaf_86325506" role="oth">ʿAqīl</persName>, brother of Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="oth">ʿAlī</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item8"><locus from="143v" to="151r">ff. 143v-151r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(h), ff. 143v-151r.</p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of the companions of Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_89661385" role="subject">Ḥusayn</persName>, younger son and successor to Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="oth">ʿAlī</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item9"><locus from="151r" to="157r">ff. 151r-157r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(i), ff. 151r-157r.</p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_89661385" role="subject">Ḥusayn</persName>, younger son and successor to Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="oth">ʿAlī</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="10" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item10"><locus from="157v" to="164v">ff. 157v-164v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(j), ff. 157v-164v.  </p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of 
                <persName key="person_f8166" role="subject">Vahb ibn ʿAbd Allāh Kalbī</persName>, companion of Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_89661385" role="oth">Ḥusayn</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="11" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item11"><locus from="164v" to="166v">ff. 164v-166v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(k), ff. 164v-166v.  </p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of 
                <persName key="person_f8167" role="subject">ʿAbd Allāh ibn Muslim ibn ʿAqīl</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><author /></msItem><msItem n="12" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item12"><locus from="166v" to="168r">ff. 166v-168r</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(l), ff. 166v-168r.</p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of ʿAbd Allāh ibn Ḥusayn, by an unnamed author.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="13" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item13"><locus from="168r" to="171v">ff. 168r-171v</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(m), ff. 168r-171v.  </p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of 
                <persName key="person_f8168" role="subject">Qāsim ibn Ḥusayn</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="14" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item14"><locus from="171v" to="1176r">ff. 171v-176r</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(n), ff. 171v-176r.  </p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of 
                <biblStruct><monogr><imprint><distributor /></imprint></monogr></biblStruct><persName key="person_f8169" role="subject">ʿAbbās ibn ʿAlī</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="15" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item15"><locus from="176v" to="182r">ff. 176v-182r</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(o), ff. 176v-182r.  </p><p>Untitled hagiographic treatise on the martyrdom of other companions of Imam 
                <persName key="viaf_89661385" role="subject">Ḥusayn</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="16" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_917-item16"><locus from="182v" to="186v">ff. 182v-186v</locus><note><p>Delhi Persian 917(p), ff. 182v-186v.  </p><p>Untitled treatise on 
                <persName key="viaf_306393875" role="subject">Shimr Z̲ī al-Jawshan</persName>, executioner of 
                <persName key="viaf_89661385" role="subject">Ḥusayn</persName>, by an unnamed author.
                        </p><p>Not dated at end.</p><p>At the end (ff. 187v-188r) are seventeen vifq al-aʿdād or magic number squares (4 x 4).</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang><note /></msItem></msContents><physDesc><objectDesc form="codex"><supportDesc material="chart"><extent>188 ff. (+1) 
